CHEM.NonStdChemComp.details: The elfamycins are so named because they exhibit antimicrobial activity through the inhibition of proteinbiosynthesis via binding to the elongation factor Tu. Known elfamycins include aurodox, C44H62N2O12; kirromycin,C43H60N2O12; azdimycin, efrotomycin,
